00065 SUMOVehicleParameter*
00066 SUMOVehicleParserHelper::parseFlowAttributes(const SUMOSAXAttributes& attrs) {
00067     bool ok = true;
00068     std::string id = attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_ID, 0, ok);
00069     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD)
00070             && attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR)) {
00071         throw ProcessError(
00072                 "At most one of '" + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD) + "' and '"
00073                         + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR)
00074                         + "' has to be given in the definition of flow '" + id
00075                         + "'.");
00076     }
00077     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD)
00078             || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR)) {
00079         if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_END)
00080                 && (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NO__DEPRECATED)
00081                         || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER))) {
00082             throw ProcessError(
00083                     "If '" + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD) + "' or '"
00084                             + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR)
00085                             + "' are given at most one of '"
00086                             + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_END) + "' and '"
00087                             + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER)
00088                             + "' are allowed in flow '" + id + "'.");
00089         }
00090     } else {
00091         if (!attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NO__DEPRECATED)
00092                 && !attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER)) {
00093             throw ProcessError(
00094                     "At least one of '" + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD)
00095                             + "', '" + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR)
00096                             + "', and '" + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER)
00097                             + "' is needed in flow '" + id + "'.");
00098         }
00099     }
00100     SUMOVehicleParameter* ret = new SUMOVehicleParameter();
00101     ret->id = id;
00102     parseCommonAttributes(attrs, ret, "flow");
00103 
00104     // parse repetition information
00105     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD)) {
00106         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_PERIODFREQ_SET;
00107 #ifdef HAVE_SUBSECOND_TIMESTEPS
00108         ret->repetitionOffset = attrs.getSUMOTimeReporting(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD,
00109                 id.c_str(), ok);
00110 #else
00111         ret->repetitionOffset = attrs.getSUMORealReporting(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD, id.c_str(), ok);
00112 #endif
00113     }
00114     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR)) {
00115         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_PERIODFREQ_SET;
00116         const SUMOReal vph = attrs.getSUMORealReporting(SUMO_ATTR_VEHSPERHOUR,
00117                 id.c_str(), ok);
00118         if (ok && vph <= 0) {
00119             delete ret;
00120             throw ProcessError(
00121                     "Invalid repetition rate in the definition of flow '" + id
00122                             + "'.");
00123         }
00124         if (ok && vph != 0) {
00125             ret->repetitionOffset = TIME2STEPS(3600. / vph);
00126         }
00127     }
00128 
00129     ret->depart = string2time(OptionsCont::getOptions().getString("begin"));
00130     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_BEGIN)) {
00131         ret->depart = attrs.getSUMOTimeReporting(SUMO_ATTR_BEGIN, id.c_str(),
00132                 ok);
00133     }
00134     if (ok && ret->depart < 0) {
00135         delete ret;
00136         throw ProcessError(
00137                 "Negative begin time in the definition of flow '" + id + "'.");
00138     }
00139     SUMOTime end = string2time(OptionsCont::getOptions().getString("end"));
00140     if (end < 0) {
00141         end = SUMOTime_MAX;
00142     }
00143     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_END)) {
00144         end = attrs.getSUMOTimeReporting(SUMO_ATTR_END, id.c_str(), ok);
00145     }
00146     if (ok && end <= ret->depart) {
00147         delete ret;
00148         throw ProcessError(
00149                 "Flow '" + id + "' ends before or at its begin time.");
00150     }
00151     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NO__DEPRECATED)
00152             || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER)) {
00153         ret->repetitionNumber =
00154                 attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER) ?
00155                         attrs.getIntReporting(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER, id.c_str(),
00156                                 ok) :
00157                         attrs.getIntReporting(SUMO_ATTR_NO__DEPRECATED,
00158                                 id.c_str(), ok);
00159         if (!gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedNumber
00160                 && attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_NO__DEPRECATED)) {
00161             gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedNumber = true;
00162             WRITE_WARNING(
00163                     "'" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_NO__DEPRECATED) + "' is deprecated, please use '" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_NUMBER) + "' instead.");
00164         }
00165         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_PERIODFREQ_SET;
00166         if (ok && ret->repetitionNumber < 0) {
00167             delete ret;
00168             throw ProcessError(
00169                     "Negative repetition number in the definition of flow '"
00170                             + id + "'.");
00171         }
00172         if (ok && ret->repetitionOffset < 0) {
00173             ret->repetitionOffset = (end - ret->depart) / ret->repetitionNumber;
00174         }
00175     } else {
00176         if (ok && ret->repetitionOffset <= 0) {
00177             delete ret;
00178             throw ProcessError(
00179                     "Invalid repetition rate in the definition of flow '" + id
00180                             + "'.");
00181         }
00182         if (end == SUMOTime_MAX) {
00183             ret->repetitionNumber = INT_MAX;
00184         } else {
00185             ret->repetitionNumber = static_cast<int>(static_cast<SUMOReal>(end
00186                     - ret->depart) / ret->repetitionOffset + 0.5);}
00187         }
00188     if (!ok) {
00189         delete ret;
00190         throw ProcessError();
00191     }
00192     return ret;
00193 }

00195 SUMOVehicleParameter*
00196 SUMOVehicleParserHelper::parseVehicleAttributes(const SUMOSAXAttributes& attrs,
00197         bool skipID, bool skipDepart) {
00198     bool ok = true;
00199     std::string id, errorMsg;
00200     if (!skipID) {
00201         id = attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_ID, 0, ok);
00202     }
00203     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD)
00204             ^ attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_REPNUMBER)) {
00205         throw ProcessError(
00206                 "The attributes '" + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD) + "' and '"
00207                         + attrs.getName(SUMO_ATTR_REPNUMBER)
00208                         + "' have to be given both in the definition of '" + id
00209                         + "'.");
00210     }
00211     SUMOVehicleParameter* ret = new SUMOVehicleParameter();
00212     ret->id = id;
00213     try {
00214         parseCommonAttributes(attrs, ret, "vehicle");
00215     } catch (ProcessError&) {
00216         delete ret;
00217         throw;
00218     }
00219     if (!skipDepart) {
00220         const std::string helper = attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_DEPART, 0,
00221                 ok);
00222         if (helper == "triggered") {
00223             ret->departProcedure = DEPART_TRIGGERED;
00224         } else {
00225             ret->departProcedure = DEPART_GIVEN;
00226             ret->depart = attrs.getSUMOTimeReporting(SUMO_ATTR_DEPART,
00227                     id.c_str(), ok);
00228             if (ok && ret->depart < 0) {
00229                 errorMsg = "Negative departure time in the definition of '" + id
00230                         + "'.";
00231                 ok = false;
00232             }
00233         }
00234     }
00235     // parse repetition information
00236     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD)) {
00237         WRITE_WARNING(
00238                 "period and repno are deprecated in vehicle '" + id + "', use flows instead.");
00239         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_PERIODFREQ_SET;
00240 #ifdef HAVE_SUBSECOND_TIMESTEPS
00241         ret->repetitionOffset = attrs.getSUMOTimeReporting(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD,
00242                 id.c_str(), ok);
00243 #else
00244         ret->repetitionOffset = attrs.getSUMORealReporting(SUMO_ATTR_PERIOD, id.c_str(), ok);
00245 #endif
00246     }
00247     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_REPNUMBER)) {
00248         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_PERIODNUM_SET;
00249         ret->repetitionNumber = attrs.getIntReporting(SUMO_ATTR_REPNUMBER,
00250                 id.c_str(), ok);
00251     }
00252 
00253     if (!ok) {
00254         delete ret;
00255         throw ProcessError(errorMsg);
00256     }
00257     return ret;
00258 }

00260 void SUMOVehicleParserHelper::parseCommonAttributes(
00261         const SUMOSAXAttributes& attrs, SUMOVehicleParameter* ret,
00262         std::string element) {
00263     //ret->refid = attrs.getStringSecure(SUMO_ATTR_REFID, "");
00264     bool ok = true;
00265     // parse route information
00266     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_ROUTE)) {
00267         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_ROUTE_SET; // !!! needed?
00268         ret->routeid = attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_ROUTE, 0, ok);
00269     }
00270     // parse type information
00271     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_TYPE)) {
00272         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_VTYPE_SET; // !!! needed?
00273         ret->vtypeid = attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_TYPE, 0, ok);
00274     }
00275     // parse line information
00276     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_LINE)) {
00277         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_LINE_SET; // !!! needed?
00278         ret->line = attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_LINE, 0, ok);
00279     }
00280     // parse zone information
00281     if ((attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ)
00282             || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ__DEPRECATED))
00283             && (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ)
00284                     || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ__DEPRECATED))) {
00285         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_TAZ_SET;
00286         ret->fromTaz =
00287                 attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ) ?
00288                         attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ, 0, ok) :
00289                         attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ__DEPRECATED,
00290                                 0, ok);
00291         ret->toTaz =
00292                 attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ) ?
00293                         attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ, 0, ok) :
00294                         attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ__DEPRECATED,
00295                                 0, ok);
00296         if (!gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedTazs
00297                 && (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ__DEPRECATED)
00298                         || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ__DEPRECATED))) {
00299             gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedTazs = true;
00300             WRITE_WARNING(
00301                     "'" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ__DEPRECATED) + "'/'" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ__DEPRECATED) + "' is deprecated, please use '" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_FROM_TAZ) + "'/'" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_TO_TAZ) + "' instead.");
00302         }
00303     }
00304     // parse reroute information
00305     if (attrs.getOptBoolReporting(SUMO_ATTR_REROUTE, 0, ok, false)) {
00306         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_FORCE_REROUTE;
00307     }
00308 
00309     // parse depart lane information
00310     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE)
00311             || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE__DEPRECATED)) {
00312         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_DEPARTLANE_SET;
00313         const std::string helper =
00314                 attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE) ?
00315                         attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE, 0, ok) :
00316                         attrs.getStringReporting(
00317                                 SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE__DEPRECATED, 0, ok);
00318         if (!gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedDepartLane
00319                 && attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE__DEPRECATED)) {
00320             gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedDepartLane = true;
00321             WRITE_WARNING(
00322                     "'" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE__DEPRECATED) + "' is deprecated, please use '" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTLANE) + "' instead.");
00323         }
00324         if (helper == "random") {
00325             ret->departLaneProcedure = DEPART_LANE_RANDOM;
00326         } else if (helper == "free") {
00327             ret->departLaneProcedure = DEPART_LANE_FREE;
00328         } else if (helper == "allowed") {
00329             ret->departLaneProcedure = DEPART_LANE_ALLOWED_FREE;
00330         } else if (helper == "best") {
00331             ret->departLaneProcedure = DEPART_LANE_BEST_FREE;
00332         } else {
00333             try {
00334                 ret->departLane = TplConvert<char>::_2int(helper.c_str());
00335                 ret->departLaneProcedure = DEPART_LANE_GIVEN;
00336                 if (ret->departLane < 0) {
00337                     throw ProcessError(
00338                             "Invalid departLane definition for " + element
00339                                     + " '" + ret->id + "'");
00340                 }
00341             } catch (NumberFormatException&) {
00342                 throw ProcessError(
00343                         "Invalid departLane definition for " + element + " '"
00344                                 + ret->id + "'");
00345             } catch (EmptyData&) {
00346                 throw ProcessError(
00347                         "Invalid departLane definition for " + element + " '"
00348                                 + ret->id + "'");
00349             }
00350         }
00351     }
00352     // parse depart position information
00353     if (attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS)
00354             || attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS__DEPRECATED)) {
00355         ret->setParameter |= VEHPARS_DEPARTPOS_SET;
00356         const std::string helper =
00357                 attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS) ?
00358                         attrs.getStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS, 0, ok) :
00359                         attrs.getStringReporting(
00360                                 SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS__DEPRECATED, 0, ok);
00361         if (!gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedDepartPos
00362                 && attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS__DEPRECATED)) {
00363             gHaveWarnedAboutDeprecatedDepartPos = true;
00364             WRITE_WARNING(
00365                     "'" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS__DEPRECATED) + "' is deprecated, please use '" + toString(SUMO_ATTR_DEPARTPOS) + "' instead.");
00366         }
00367         if (helper == "random") {
00368             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_RANDOM;
00369         } else if (helper == "random_free") {
00370             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_RANDOM_FREE;
00371         } else if (helper == "free") {
00372             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_FREE;
00373         } else if (helper == "base") {
00374             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_BASE;
00375         } else if (helper == "pwagSimple") {
00376             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_PWAG_SIMPLE;
00377         } else if (helper == "pwagGeneric") {
00378             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_PWAG_GENERIC;

00380             ret->departPosProcedure = DEPART_POS_MAX_SPEED_GAP;

00761 
00762 void SUMOVehicleParserHelper::parseVTypeEmbedded(SUMOVTypeParameter& into,
00763         int element, const SUMOSAXAttributes& attrs, bool fromVType) {
00764     const CFAttrMap& allowedAttrs = getAllowedCFModelAttrs();
00765     CFAttrMap::const_iterator cf_it;
00766     for (cf_it = allowedAttrs.begin(); cf_it != allowedAttrs.end(); cf_it++) {
00767         if (cf_it->first == element) {
00768             break;
00769         }
00770     }
00771     if (cf_it == allowedAttrs.end()) {
00772         if (SUMOXMLDefinitions::Tags.has(element)) {
00773             WRITE_WARNING(
00774                     "Unknown cfmodel " + toString((SumoXMLTag)element) + " when parsing vtype '" + into.id + "'");
00775         } else {
00776             WRITE_WARNING(
00777                     "Unknown cfmodel when parsing vtype '" + into.id + "'");
00778         }
00779     }
00780     if (!fromVType) {
00781         into.cfModel = cf_it->first;
00782     }
00783     bool ok = true;
00784     for (std::set<SumoXMLAttr>::const_iterator it = cf_it->second.begin();
00785             it != cf_it->second.end(); it++) {
00786         if (attrs.hasAttribute(*it)) {
00787             into.cfParameter[*it] = attrs.getSUMORealReporting(*it,
00788                     into.id.c_str(), ok);
00789         }
00790     }
00791     if (!ok) {
00792         throw ProcessError();
00793     }
00794 }

00852 SUMOVehicleClass SUMOVehicleParserHelper::parseVehicleClass(
00853         const SUMOSAXAttributes& attrs, const std::string& id) {
00854     SUMOVehicleClass vclass = SVC_UNKNOWN;
00855     try {
00856         bool ok = true;
00857         std::string vclassS =
00858                 attrs.hasAttribute(SUMO_ATTR_VCLASS) ?
00859                         attrs.getOptStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_VCLASS,
00860                                 id.c_str(), ok, "") :
00861                         attrs.getOptStringReporting(
00862                                 SUMO_ATTR_VCLASS__DEPRECATED, id.c_str(), ok,
00863                                 "");
00864         if (vclassS == "") {
00865             return vclass;
00866         }
00867         return getVehicleClassID(vclassS);
00868     } catch (...) {
00869         WRITE_ERROR(
00870                 "The class for " + attrs.getObjectType() + " '" + id + "' is not known.");
00871     }
00872     return vclass;
00873 }

00893 SUMOVehicleShape SUMOVehicleParserHelper::parseGuiShape(
00894         const SUMOSAXAttributes& attrs, const std::string& id) {
00895     bool ok = true;
00896     std::string vclassS = attrs.getOptStringReporting(SUMO_ATTR_GUISHAPE,
00897             id.c_str(), ok, "");
00898     if (SumoVehicleShapeStrings.hasString(vclassS)) {
00899         return SumoVehicleShapeStrings.get(vclassS);
00900     } else {
00901         WRITE_ERROR(
00902                 "The shape '" + vclassS + "' for " + attrs.getObjectType() + " '" + id + "' is not known.");
00903         return SVS_UNKNOWN;
